description._content: Catalog #: 09_01912 Title: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo San Bernardino California Additional Information: Clarence S. Irvine (second from right) being welcomed by three men in military uniform to Norton Air Force Base in San Bernardino California. March 1959, Brigadier General Clarence Irvine enjoyed a long distinguished military career, mainly involving engineering. He served with the XXI Bomber Command (B-29's) during WWII and continued to serve throughout the 1950s and 1960s. Tags: Brigadier General Clarence S.
